The paper deals with similarity search algorithms in graph databases, which are commonly used in data management and analytics. The paper discusses the problem of representation independence, which is the property of similarity search algorithms to return essentially the same answers over different databases that represent the same information. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
